00:52:30.397 --> 00:52:33.149  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to think that they're gonna make it
through this event.

756
00:52:33.817 --> 00:52:36.820  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>But at the same time,</i>
<i>we've tried so hard to capture this.</i>

757
00:52:38.280 --> 00:52:40.615  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We essentially had</i>
<i>to make a difficult decision</i>

758
00:52:40.699 --> 00:52:45.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to stick to our original plan,</i>
<i>with less-than-ideal odds,</i>

759
00:52:45.787 --> 00:52:49.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>or we go check out some of these</i>
<i>other portions of the Great Barrier Reef</i>

760
00:52:49.457 --> 00:52:50.917  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>that were getting really warm.</i>

761
00:52:52.127 --> 00:52:54.254  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It's all of this to the north
of New Caledonia

762
00:52:54.337 --> 00:52:57.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
and below and even these splotch areas
are at Level 2.

763
00:52:58.133 --> 00:53:02.095  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
It's just... nothing short of catastrophic
for the coral.

764
00:53:03.471 --> 00:53:06.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Orlowski] <i>We know now</i>
<i>New Caledonia is bleaching.</i>

765
00:53:06.683 --> 00:53:08.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Lizard Island is bleaching.</i>

766
00:53:09.644 --> 00:53:12.022  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I guess it is a simple decision
in some ways.

767
00:53:12.105 --> 00:53:16.151  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
We should just pick up and move over,
and reset up at those new locations.

768
00:53:17.068 --> 00:53:18.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The problem is the time-lapse cameras.</i>

769
00:53:19.487 --> 00:53:24.075  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It'll take weeks to move those systems,</i>
<i>and we'll have missed the bleaching.</i>

770
00:53:26.620 --> 00:53:28.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We're gonna have</i>
<i>to figure something else out.</i>

771
00:53:31.041 --> 00:53:34.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Ackerman] <i>I went to turn my computer off,</i>
<i>and there was this message from Jeff,</i>

772
00:53:34.252 --> 00:53:36.338  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
saying, "How soon can you pack?"

773
00:53:38.465 --> 00:53:41.760  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We were gonna abandon</i>
<i>these camera systems...</i>

774
00:53:42.719 --> 00:53:48.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and do manual underwater
time-lapses every single day.

775
00:53:48.308 --> 00:53:51.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think we, as a team,
realized that there was no going back.

776
00:53:53.980 --> 00:53:55.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Rago] <i>We headed up to Lizard Island,</i>

777
00:53:55.607 --> 00:53:58.443  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>and the other portion of our team</i>
<i>went out to New Caledonia.</i>

778
00:54:46.366 --> 00:54:47.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's the most amazing reef.</i>

779
00:54:48.076 --> 00:54:49.953  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And it's just demolished.</i>

780
00:54:52.872 --> 00:54:53.957  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's just so hot.

781
00:54:55.125 --> 00:54:57.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Like, it literally feels like a bathtub.

782
00:55:08.096 --> 00:55:10.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Anybody order a large Coke?

783
00:55:12.267 --> 00:55:14.728  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Here we are talking
about coral reef bleaching

784
00:55:14.811 --> 00:55:16.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and global climate change...

785
00:55:17.022 --> 00:55:18.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and here's our other problem.

786
00:55:19.774 --> 00:55:21.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>When we went to Lizard Island,</i>

787
00:55:21.943 --> 00:55:24.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
we didn't have
our time-lapse cameras anymore.

788
00:55:24.821 --> 00:55:27.365  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Orlowski] <i>The idea is to take one tripod</i>
<i>and one camera,</i>

789
00:55:27.449 --> 00:55:29.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and get as many shots as we can</i>
<i>in as many positions</i>

790
00:55:29.951 --> 00:55:34.622  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>of as many pieces of coral as we can,</i>
<i>and to repeat that every single day.</i>

791
00:55:34.706 --> 00:55:38.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Rago] <i>Get on the boat at 9:15,</i>
<i>go out to your first site.</i>

792
00:55:40.378 --> 00:55:43.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You would find your markings</i>
<i>for the tripod,</i>

793
00:55:43.298 --> 00:55:45.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>put down each leg at the correct heights,</i>

794
00:55:45.258 --> 00:55:49.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and then you would have reference points</i>
<i>you could then attach the laser beams to,</i>

795
00:55:49.637 --> 00:55:52.766  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and then I had a lamination</i>
<i>of the first day's shots.</i>

796
00:55:52.849 --> 00:55:55.060  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And then you would take</i>
<i>two minutes of footage,</i>

797
00:55:55.143 --> 00:55:56.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>then you'd pick everything back up,</i>

798
00:55:57.020 --> 00:55:59.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>move onto the next site,</i>
<i>and do the same again.</i>

799
00:55:59.314 --> 00:56:00.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And then again and again.</i>

800
00:56:00.815 --> 00:56:03.234  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And you do that essentially</i>
<i>25 times a day.</i>

801
00:56:04.611 --> 00:56:07.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Between Jeff and I, we had 60 sites.</i>

802
00:56:10.241 --> 00:56:13.912  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The reason we built the time-lapse systems
was it seemed absurd

803
00:56:13.995 --> 00:56:16.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to have people camped on the beach
at multiple locations

804
00:56:16.831 --> 00:56:19.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and having to go down</i>
<i>and do what a machine is designed to do.</i>

805
00:56:20.627 --> 00:56:22.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Rago] <i>Logistically, it was a nightmare.</i>

806
00:56:22.670 --> 00:56:26.216  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Getting it in the right position,</i>
<i>and you're fighting the current,</i>

807
00:56:26.299 --> 00:56:28.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>so you're getting bounced around a lot,</i>

808
00:56:28.301 --> 00:56:33.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>your knees are bleeding everywhere,</i>
<i>your body is cut up, you're tired.</i>

809
00:56:36.601 --> 00:56:39.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It got to the point where you're</i>
<i>spending four hours a day underwater.</i>

810
00:56:40.063 --> 00:56:41.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Weird things start happening.</i>

811
00:56:43.983 --> 00:56:45.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Mendelow] <i>I don't know if it's funny.</i>

812
00:56:47.112 --> 00:56:48.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's, uh...

813
00:56:48.822 --> 00:56:50.490  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You do what you have to do.

814
00:57:35.368 --> 00:57:38.872  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
[Vevers] <i>We were getting reports</i>
<i>that the corals in New Caledonia</i>

815
00:57:38.955 --> 00:57:41.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
<i>were doing something completely weird.</i>

816
00:57:44.085 --> 00:57:47.213  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ackerman] <i>Richard was there, he said,</i>
<i>"It's the craziest thing I've ever seen.</i>

817
00:57:47.297 --> 00:57:48.590  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I don't know what it is."</i>

818
00:57:48.673 --> 00:57:50.592  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The locals didn't know what it was.</i>

819
00:57:52.844 --> 00:57:54.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>We didn't know what was happening.</i>

820
00:57:56.139 --> 00:57:57.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I asked Richard to explain.

821
00:57:57.474 --> 00:57:59.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He's like, "Don't know what to tell you.
It's glowing."

822
00:58:20.288 --> 00:58:22.332  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Vevers] <i>This was different.</i>

823
00:58:24.751 --> 00:58:26.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The corals were... were fluorescing.</i>

824
00:58:29.547 --> 00:58:34.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They're producing a chemical sunscreen</i>
<i>to protect themselves from the heat.</i>

825
00:58:38.389 --> 00:58:39.933  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>You can't even describe it.</i>

826
00:58:43.311 --> 00:58:45.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>They were the most vivid colors</i>
<i>I've ever seen.</i>

827
00:59:02.580 --> 00:59:06.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is the most beautiful transformation</i>
<i>in nature.</i>

828
00:59:08.211 --> 00:59:11.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>The incredibly beautiful phase of death.</i>

829
00:59:15.093 --> 00:59:16.886  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And it feels as if...</i>

830
00:59:17.762 --> 00:59:20.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>it's the corals saying:</i>

831
00:59:20.390 --> 00:59:21.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>"Look at me.</i>

832
00:59:24.185 --> 00:59:25.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Please, notice."</i>

833
01:00:14.527 --> 01:00:16.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Ackerman] <i>We were diving every day</i>
<i>from a floating restaurant.</i>

834
01:00:19.157 --> 01:00:20.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[dance music playing over speakers]

835
01:00:20.950 --> 01:00:24.078  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was kind of funny, the first day.

836
01:00:27.123 --> 01:00:30.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Like, that whole thought</i>
<i>just became much more depressing.</i>

837
01:00:33.546 --> 01:00:34.380  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bit of a shock.

838
01:00:45.433 --> 01:00:50.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>This is one of the rarest events</i>
<i>in nature happening...</i>

839
01:00:51.064 --> 01:00:53.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and everyone's just oblivious to it.</i>

840
01:00:59.739 --> 01:01:02.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And you can't blame them for it.</i>
<i>I mean, it's... It's just...</i>

841
01:01:04.369 --> 01:01:07.372  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>almost typical of all of humanity.</i>

842
01:01:09.916 --> 01:01:11.084  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>This is going on...</i>

843
01:01:12.085 --> 01:01:13.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and no one is noticing.</i>

844
01:01:21.260 --> 01:01:23.096  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Rago] <i>We designed something originally</i>

845
01:01:23.179 --> 01:01:26.057  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to do this project without emotions.

846
01:01:26.724 --> 01:01:30.103  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And when we began doing this manually
at Lizard Island...

847
01:01:30.895 --> 01:01:32.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
you have the emotional ties to it.

848
01:01:32.563 --> 01:01:33.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are down there.

849
01:01:33.606 --> 01:01:35.733  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And to sit there for a month,

850
01:01:35.817 --> 01:01:40.071  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and every single day,
watch something new around you die

851
01:01:40.154 --> 01:01:41.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you saw yesterday...

852
01:01:42.907 --> 01:01:43.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>it's just difficult.</i>

853
01:02:09.976 --> 01:02:11.894  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You forget what it looked like</i>
<i>at the beginning.</i>

854
01:02:13.146 --> 01:02:16.065  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>And some days, when you go back,</i>

855
01:02:16.149 --> 01:02:18.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and you're sitting down there,</i>
<i>looking at it now,</i>

856
01:02:18.443 --> 01:02:19.610  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and it doesn't look real.</i>

857
01:02:21.571 --> 01:02:24.198  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you-- It's not even--
You can't even accept it.

858
01:02:28.494 --> 01:02:32.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And then you open your eyes,</i>
<i>and it's dead as far as you can see.</i>

859
01:02:56.814 --> 01:02:59.942  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's algae and dead coral skeletons.</i>

860
01:03:34.894 --> 01:03:38.648  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It's flesh.</i>
<i>It's living tissue... that's rotting away.</i>

861
01:03:45.112 --> 01:03:46.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>It's disgusting, really.</i>

862
01:04:29.657 --> 01:04:30.658  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

863
01:04:38.499 --> 01:04:40.501  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I thought we would find bleaching.</i>

864
01:04:42.128 --> 01:04:43.838  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought we would capture it.

865
01:04:44.505 --> 01:04:48.050  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But I don't think I ever prepared myself,

866
01:04:48.134 --> 01:04:50.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or thought we were gonna see this.

867
01:05:00.229 --> 01:05:03.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
See, I'm not even mad that I'm leaving,
because it's just so miserable here.

868
01:05:06.152 --> 01:05:06.986  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sniffles]

869
01:05:38.976 --> 01:05:40.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Marshall] <i>When coral bleaches and dies...</i>

870
01:05:41.312 --> 01:05:42.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>you're losing the coral animal.</i>

871
01:05:43.022 --> 01:05:45.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>And that's a shame,</i>
<i>'cause it's a beautiful thing.</i>

872
01:05:45.441 --> 01:05:50.529  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But a coral is... a fundamental part
of a huge ecosystem.

873
01:05:51.238 --> 01:05:54.033  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It is, in a way,
just like the trees in a forest.

874
01:05:54.825 --> 01:05:57.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If coral reefs are lost,</i>
<i>we're affecting the life</i>

875
01:05:57.912 --> 01:05:59.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>of a quarter of the ocean.</i>

876
01:06:00.957 --> 01:06:03.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>If the little fish disappear,</i>
<i>the big fish disappear,</i>

877
01:06:03.334 --> 01:06:05.836  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and then you can look at humans</i>
<i>as one of the big fish.</i>

878
01:06:10.299 --> 01:06:14.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[Porter] <i>It's easy to think about the fate</i>
<i>of an individual species.</i>

879
01:06:15.763 --> 01:06:18.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>But what is a little harder to explain...</i>

880
01:06:19.058 --> 01:06:23.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
it's the beginning
